\begin_layout Enumerate
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $f(\begin{bmatrix}x\\
t
\end{bmatrix})=\frac{Ax+b}{ct+d},$
\end_inset

such that 
\begin_inset Formula $dom(f)=\{\begin{bmatrix}x\\
t
\end{bmatrix}|\ ct+d>0\}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Solution:
\]

\end_inset

Let 
\begin_inset Formula $S\subset\RR^{d}$
\end_inset

 be a convex set, show that 
\begin_inset Formula $\{f(x)\ |\ x\in S\ \cap\ dom(f)\}$
\end_inset

 is convex.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Lets take the hints suggestion and look at 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{1}=\{\begin{bmatrix}A & 0\\
0 & c
\end{bmatrix}\cdot\begin{bmatrix}x\\
t
\end{bmatrix}+\begin{bmatrix}b\\
d
\end{bmatrix}\ \ |\ \ \begin{bmatrix}x\\
t
\end{bmatrix}\in S\}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Notice that 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 is convex, and the operation 
\begin_inset Formula $\begin{bmatrix}A & 0\\
0 & c
\end{bmatrix}\cdot\begin{bmatrix}x\\
t
\end{bmatrix}+\begin{bmatrix}b\\
d
\end{bmatrix}$
\end_inset

 is affine, meaning 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{1}$
\end_inset

is a set of affine operation on a convex set - this is a convex set as well,
 and so 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{1}$
\end_inset

 is convex.
 This means that the enumerator if our output of 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 is convex.
 The denominator is clearly affine as well, and since 
\begin_inset Formula $ct+d>0$
\end_inset

 is required in 
\begin_inset Formula $dom(f)$
\end_inset

 we get that 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 is a composition of an 2 affine transformation, and packing them into a
 perspective function.
 Fortunately, 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 is convex, and a composition of affine functions, and perspective conserves
 convexity, and so 
\begin_inset Formula $\{f(x)\ |\ x\in S\ \cap\ dom(f)\}$
\end_inset

 is convex.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
