\begin_inset Formula $v\in V$
\end_inset

 and let 
\begin_inset Formula $o$
\end_inset

 be in 
\begin_inset Formula $V's$
\end_inset

 orthogonal complement, then 
\begin_inset Formula $\li v,o\ri=0$
\end_inset

 by definitions, and so 
\begin_inset Formula $o\in V^{*}\rightarrow V^{*}=$
\end_inset

orthogonal complement of 
\begin_inset Formula $V$
\end_inset

.
